# Trilingual Comment Standard

For every line of code in this project, add inline comments in this format:

## C# files
// actual C# code
// Python: <equivalent Python code>
// R: <equivalent R code>
// WHAT: one sentence — what this line does
// WHY: one sentence — why it's written this way
// SYNTAX: (optional) explain non-obvious tokens/operators

## Python files
actual Python code
C#: <equivalent C# code>
R: <equivalent R code>
WHAT: one sentence
WHY: one sentence
SYNTAX: (optional)

## R files
actual R code
Python: <equivalent Python code>
C#: <equivalent C# code>
WHAT: one sentence
WHY: one sentence
SYNTAX: (optional)

## Rules
- Never skip a line — comments go on EVERY line including imports and braces
- Keep equivalents as real runnable code, not descriptions
- If no equivalent exists in a language, write: # No direct equivalent — explain why
- WHAT/WHY max 1 sentence each
- SYNTAX note only when a token/operator would confuse a learner
